# Python
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/

# Toolchain (downloaded by setup.sh)
.toolchain/

# Vendored as submodule (initialized in Phase 4). No trailing slash so the
# pattern matches both the cloned directory in the main repo AND the
# symlink that worktree.py creates inside each worktree (otherwise git
# status flags the symlink as untracked and sandbox check trips).
formal/riscv-formal

# Formal run output (regenerated per run; surfaced via stdout to the orchestrator).
# Glob covers both the legacy single-file path and the PID-suffixed variants
# emitted by run_all.sh after the concurrent-rm-race fix (formal/run_all.sh
# writes last_run-<pid>.log so simultaneous invocations don't truncate each
# other). Without the glob, `git status` lists the per-PID logs as untracked
# and the scribe-phase sandbox check rolls back the scribe's commit.
formal/last_run*.log

# Orchestrator-emitted per-rep summary. Phase-2 contract output written
# by tools/orchestrator.py:write_run_summary after every round and at
# end of main(). Derivable from log.jsonl; not worth tracking in git.
# Without this entry, `git status` between rounds shows it as untracked
# (since the orchestrator never `git add`s it), and the hypothesis-phase
# sandbox check in tools/agents/hypothesis.py rolls back the next slot's
# turn with "modified off-limits paths: ['.../run_summary.json']".
# Caught live during the gpt-5.5 effort sweep — slot 2 in round 2 of
# every rep was hypothesis_gen_failed for this reason.
cores/*/experiments/run_summary.json

# Agent stdout capture, written per-worktree by tools/agents/implement.py
# and per-hypothesis by tools/agents/hypothesis.py for `tail -f` visibility
# into Phase 1 and Phase 2. Untracked so the orchestrator's sandbox check
# (offlimits_changes, orchestrator.py:42) doesn't see it as an off-limits
# agent edit. .claude.log kept for back-compat with legacy worktree logs.
.agent.log
.agent.last
.agent.*.log
.agent.*.last
.claude.log
.scribe.log
.scribe.*.last

# Build artifacts
out/
generated/
sim_build/
test/cosim/obj_dir/
test/cosim/sim_build/
test/**/sim_build/
test/*.result.xml
test/results.xml
cores/*/test/*.result.xml
*.vcd
*.fst
*.gtkw

# Bench ELFs (rebuild from sources)
bench/programs/*.elf
bench/programs/*.o
bench/programs/*.bin
bench/programs/*.hex

# Experiment artifacts.
# - log.jsonl IS tracked: orchestrator's authoritative journal of every
#   iteration (accept/regression/broken). Rejected hypotheses never
#   produce an implementation commit so the log is the only record.
#   Auto-committed by tools/orchestrator.py:append_log() per iteration.
# - progress.png IS tracked: it's the chart embedded in README.md, so
#   the latest state is always viewable from GitHub. Regenerated and
#   auto-committed alongside log.jsonl.
# - per-iteration worktrees and per-iteration hypothesis YAMLs are
#   transient inputs/outputs of the loop, not source of truth.

# Per-core gitignored paths (Phase C)
cores/*/worktrees/
cores/*/generated/
cores/*/obj_dir/
cores/*/implementation_notes.md
cores/*/experiments/hypotheses/
cores/*/experiments/hypotheses/*.yml
cores/*/experiments/hypotheses/*.yaml

# Editor / OS
.DS_Store
*.swp
.idea/
.vscode/

# Claude Code workspace
.claude/
docs/assets/

# Local git worktrees (subagent-driven dev; not the orchestrator's experiments/worktrees)
.worktrees/

# Node deps for bench-fence pi extension (installed locally for typecheck;
# pi handles installs at run time so the deps don't need to be committed).
node_modules/

# Pi-coding-agent session storage inside per-rep clones.
.pi-sessions/

# Per-rep agent telemetry inside bench/ — large, regenerable.
# Top-level results.jsonl + LEADERBOARD.md ARE checked in.
bench/*/rep*/log.jsonl
bench/*/rep*/agent.log

# Throwaway harness-verification runs (one-model YAMLs + their output
# trees). These are reliability checks, not benchmark data — output is
# regenerable and the YAMLs only encode "rerun this single model to
# confirm a fix landed". Naming convention: `*-verify` for output dirs,
# `models-*-verify.yaml` for the throwaway model YAML.
bench/*-verify/
bench/smoke-*/
tools/bench/models-*-verify.yaml
